inn1.comm: gets behind a short in length delivery and plays behind square leg
defends to the on side
moves forward in line to a good length delivery and defends to cover
good delivery angled across, Watson plays and misses, there was good movement there
it was short in length angled across, this time Watson watches it closely and lets it go
pushes firmly down the track to the right of mid off, who does well to prevent any run
on the legs, off the pad to fine leg for a leg bye
short in length outside the off stump, moves away after pitching, Watson shoulders arms
short in length once again outside the off stump, moves away, left alone
moves forward to a fuller delivery and drives well wide of mid off for the first run off the bat
on the pads, Katich misses the tickle down to fine leg, off the pad to the on side
moves forward and defends it beside the track on the on side
in the channel outside the off stump, hit past backward point
length-delivery on the leg and middle, pushed to the on side and they cross over for a quick single
probing delivery just outside the off stump, Katich watches it carefully and shoulders arms
another length-delivery just on the off stump, coming in with the angle, turned to the on side
back of length, on the leg and middle and it went down, with the angle.
on the off and middle, full in length, pushed towards extra cover
full in length, on the off, Watson leans forward and pushes it towards cover
whistling through the corridor outside off, left alone
another one floating in the channel, left alone again
good delivery . This one came in slightly after pitching on a length around the off stump line, Watson comes forward and stabs at it and the ball rolls over towards square-leg
pushed back down the track
Watson ends the over with a crash over covers. It was full and outside the off stump, line and length inviting a drive, Watson obliges and takes the aerial route.
lands outside the off stump and veers further away, Katich raises his bat, watches it all the way into Baugh's gloves
fullish on the off and middle, Katich is slightly late in coming forward, and pushes it to the on side
lovely delivery that almost squared-up Katich. It landed on a length, on the off stump line, and seamed away a bit
lands on the same spot but this one just holds the line, Katich stands tall to punch it back down the track
length-delivery on the middle, Katich shuffles inside the line, works it towards midwicket
wide down the leg side. The right-hand bat comes on for the first time in the over and that seems to have put Bradshaw off.
almost a wide outside the off stump but Watson reaches for it to cut, makes contact with the bottom-half of the bat and the ball rolls over to point
on the legs, tried to turn it around the corner, doesn't connect and the ball rolls off the pads towards shortish fine-leg
Ah.. they just move in a man close on the on side and Smith offers a lollypop full and well outside the off stump, driven through covers
gets the radar right, on the off and middle, pushed back down the track
Watson goes down on his knee, reaches out for a fullish delivery well outside the off stump and creams it over cover.
on the off stump line, Watson taps it close on the off side - squarish point- and they cross over for a quick single
beaten...  just short of driveable length, outside the off stump and Katich is caught at the crease, just pushes at it...
good-length delivery on the leg and middle, Katich tries to flick it , his head falls over in the process, and doesn't connect and is rapped on the pads
length delivery on the middle and leg, tries to work it on the on side, misses, gets rapped on the pads
this time he connects and works it past square-leg
on the legs, Katich shuffles across, tickles it down to fine-leg

almost played on..... It was full in length, landed on the off and straightened, Watson shapes up for a cut, and as the ball veers in and cramps him, he stabs at it and the inside-edge takes the ball dangerously close to the stumps

gone this time. It was a length delivery angling across, Watson doesn't quite manage to shift his balance to his back foot but attempts a forcing shot, and edges it straight to Chris Gayle at first slip. Bradshaw gets his man. A nice probing line and length.
fullish, on the leg and middle, turned to square-leg
angled across Katich who leans forward, and shoulders arms
shuffles across and offers the dead-bat to a full-length delivery on the middle
full and outside the off stump, inviting a drive, Katich doesn't indulge, gets across to the line of the ball and pushes it to cover point
length delivery on the off , again slanting across, Katich punches it towards mid-off
angled across, and left alone
almost carried to first slip. It was full and pushed across, Ponting lunges forward and ends up pushing inside the line, gets an outside edge.
fullish on the legs, Ponting again lunges forward, tries to work it to the on side, misses, the ball rolls off the pads
in the channel outside the off stump and Katich, as he has been doing throughout his painful vigil, lets it go
another one outside the off, left alone
on the middle, worked to the on side
lands outside the off stump on a length, and moves away, Katich pushes at it, away from his body, and the ball rolls over towards cover
probing delivery just outside the off stump, Ponting shuffles across, covers the stumps, shoulders arms
just short of driveable length, on the middle, pushed towards mid-off

super fielding and almost produces a run-out. slightly back of length, outside the off stump and Ponting cuts. The ball bounces over the left shoulder of Bravo at point who stretches his left hand, makes the half-stop. they stutter through for  a single, after hesitation and Katich makes in time to beat the Bravo throw
fullish and on the legs, flicked through midwicket
Katich moves to 4 off 28 deliveries
length-delivery on the off, coming in a touch, turned to midwicket
another good-length delivery on the off and middle, Katich shuffles across and pushes it towards mid-on
outside the off stump, back of a length, swatted away to cover point
in that corridor outside off - good tight over in progress- and punched towards cover
sails past the off stump, left alone by Katich
fullish and on the middle, Katich works it past midwicket to retain the strike. Is it good or bad news for Australia?! Katich is lolling on 5 from 34 balls.
short and outside the leg stump, should have been pulled away for a boundary. Katich attempts to do it, the ball bounds off the back of the bat and drops on the off side
turned to midwicket
full and slanted across, Katich has a stab at it, away from his body, gets an inside-edge that takes the ball to fine-leg
fullish on the middle and leg, turned past square-leg

almost a run-out. Katich pushes a fullish delivery on the off, to the right of Sarwan, at mid-off, and they take off for a single. Sarwan swoops on the ball and has a shy at the non-striker's end but Katich hurls himself and makes it in time. Just.
just outside the off stump, cut to point
hit through the line, but no power behind that stroke and the ball rolls over to mid-off
shuffles across his stumps and turns a ball on the middle, down to fine-leg
pushed across Ponting who lets it go through..
slower ball, outside the off stump, Ponting waits for it , opens the face of the blade and runs it down to third-man
leans forward  to a length-delivery on the off and drives it towards extra cover
kicks up off a length and Ponting hops back, feet in the air, and keeps it down

The previous one had kicked up, but this one kept a touch low after landing on a length in the off and middle line. Ponting makes the fatal mistake of going back instead of leaning forward and is surprised by the lack of bounce. He tries to get his bat down in line but as it often happens in such occasions, he brings it across the line and the ball whistles past the desperate wave of the blade and thuds into his back pad.
right up there, almost at the block-hole, on the off , pushed to point
slightly back of a length, outside the off stump, steered to point
leans forward and pats it towards cover
pitches wide outside off stump, cut down to third man for one
straighter line on middle and off stump, the batsman comes forward and defends on the front foot
a touch shorter outside off stump, Martyn uses the width, leans into the cover drive and caresses it to the fence
left alone outside off stump
shorter length and drifting on to the pads, flicked off the pads to fine leg
angling into Katich from outside off stump, the batsman goes play and tries to play it on the leg side but gets hit on the pad
full and angling into middle stump, dug out to mid-on
drifting on to the pads on this occasion, Martyn flicks to square leg where the fielder fumbles, the batsmen initially want the run but decide against it
on the legs again, flicked through the vacant midwicket region
on the off and middle, Martyn leans forward slightly and offers the full-face of the bat in defense
on the middle and leg, full in length, punched to mid-on
length delivery on the off, Martyn leans forward, plays it with soft hands, towards left of mid-off and they cross over for a single.
on target rightaway, on that off stump line, pushed to cover
slightly outside the off stump, full in length, Martyn keeps his left foot out, waits for the ball to arrive, opens the face of the blade and steers it to backward point
shuffles across to a fullish delivery on the middle and off and drives it past the bowler and mid-off makes the stop.
right up there, played inside-out to cover point
short of length, outside the off stump, Katich cuts it right of Bravo, at point, who fumbles and they cross over for a single.
on the hips, Martyn turns it past the square-leg
short of length, just outside the off stump, Martyn pushes at it, bat away from his body, and the ball rolls over to point
back of length, just outside the off, Martyn doesn't move towards the ball, stands there and punches at it, and very good diving stop at cover prevents any chance of a run
on the off, pushed to cover
short and outside the off stump, Martyn square-drives it on the up, past point
from round the wickets, fullish just outside the off, Katich square-drives to left of point where Bravo flings himself to make a good stop.
driven to mid-off. Katich has faced 50 deliveries now and is lolling on 11.
short and outside the off stump, square-driven past point and Morton runs across from wide third-man and makes a good diving stop near the ropes
this time there is no chance for Morton. The square-drives takes the ball to the right of point and thats that.
short and angling across Katich who cuts it. No real power behind that stroke and Bravo, at point,  moves to his right to make the stop and has a shy at the striker's end.
length delivery on the off, Martyn, who doesn't move forward all that much, stabs at with slightly opened face of the bat and the ball rolls over towards point
Bravo continues with his good work. Short and outside off, Martyn cuts only to find Bravo diving to his right to prevent a certain four.
hit the deck around back of length, on the off and Martyn taps it towards cover
comes in a touch after landing outside the off stump on a length, pushed to the left of mid-off and they hurry through for a quick single
full and on the legs, tries to flick it away, misses and the ball rolls off the pads to shortish fine-leg
full and on the middle and leg, turned to square-leg
length delivery, on the off and middle, Katich tries to turn it to the on side, misses and the ball rolls off the thigh pad
Katich breaks free! right in the slot outside the off stump and Katich hits through the line and it sails over long-off.
pushed back down the track
length-delivery on the middle and leg, and it comes in a touch. Katich shuffles across, pats it back to Bravo who fields and takes a few steps towards Katich and stares. Katich stares back.
swatted away to cover
beaten outside the off. length-delivery in the channel and Martyn tries to run it down to third-man, misses.
back of length, outside the off, room for Martyn to unfurl his square-cut.
closer to the off and full in length, punched past cover, out to the sweeper.
on the hips, turned past square-leg
yorker and it almost got through. Martyn gets his bat down in time to dig it out.
fullish, outside the off, steered to cover point
from round the wickets, coming in from outside the off stump, defended off the front foot
overpitched on the middle and leg, turned away with a flick of the wrists, to the left of mid-on
leans forward, head over the ball and dead-bats it
on the hips, Martyn tries to flick it away, doesn't connect and the ball thuds into the thigh-pad
slightly slower delivery, just outside the off stump, steered to cover point
almost a off break, lands outside the leg, breaks in and raps Katich on the pads as he unsuccessfully attempts to work it to the on side
on the legs, turned to deep midwicket
floated on the middle and leg, pushed back down the track
beaten in flight. Katich pushes hard at a delivery which has been held back a bit and the edge takes the ball towards short third-man

Katich's painful vigil ends. The ball stops on him after landing on a length just outside the off and Katich goes through with his shot. Ends up scooping it in the air and to long-off where Samuels runs in a few yards and stoops low to take the catch
turned to the on side
on a length, around the middle and off, patted back down the track
bit of width outside off, cut away to point
fuller and coming in from outside the off stump, Symonds gets his left foot out and  plays it quietly to the off side
keeps a touch low after landing on a length outside the off stump, Symonds gets his bat down in a hurry and pushes it towards cover
in the corridor outside off, comes in off the seam, left alone

huge shout for lbw but turned down.  It landed on a length, just outside the off stump and jagged back in to catch Symonds by surprise. Maybe, the point of impact was outside the off stump. Shall report after the replays
floated on the off and middle, patted back down the track
wide down the leg side. landed on the leg stump line and turned away
outside the off, played back to the bowler
fires in a 88kmph delivery on the off stump line and beats Symonds. But again the point of impact was outside the off and so he escapes
on the legs, worked around the corner to short fine-leg
on the off stump, Martyn backs away and attempts to late-cut but can't beat the short third-man
seams in after landing full in length just outside the off stump and driven to mid-on
again lands on a length on the off but holds its line this time and Symonds gets an outside edge as he pushes inside the line
fullish and on the legs, should have been put away but maybe, he is beaten by the late swing. Raps him on the pads.
outside the off stump, delivered from a slightly round-armish action, swatted away to the third-man region
probing on that off stump line, at times he gets it to tail in. This one did but Symonds is right behind that one and offers the full face of the bat in defense
slants it in, full in length, turned past square-leg
outside the off stump, Symonds leans forward and pats it to the off side
pre-determined paddle sweep is out and they take a single
swept from the stumps, to long-leg
drags it short, almost a long-hop, pulled straight to the deep midwicket fielder.
full and on the middle, driven down the ground to long-on
on the off stump line, punched towards mid-off
fuller and outside the off, steered to backward point
half-edged and half-steered to the third-man fence. It was full and outside the off, Martyn attempts to run it down to third-man.
fullish, on the off stump, Martyn doesn't move his feet forward, just leans forward, shifting his balance forward and dead-bats it away
comes in a touch from just outside the off and Martyn is beaten as he tries to cut it late
wide down the leg side. Wanted to slant it in but the wrist-position went awry at the release
in the channel outside off, pushed to point
gets beaten as he attempts to paddle-sweep it around the corner
outside edge takes the ball past the short third-man
driven to mid-on
comes down the track but Gayle drags back the length and Symonds adjusts to push it to the off side.
turned to the on side
spears that one full and straight on the off, pushed to cover point
fullish on the legs, worked to deep midwicket
yorker on the off, dug out to point
fullish on the legs, flicked behind square-leg

full and just outside the off, Martyn doesn't move his feet - this is not said as criticism oh Martyn fans, just describing! - and opens the face of the bat and makes contact and runs it down to third-man
square-cut to the sweeper cover
patted to short third-man
lands outside the off, turns in and cramps Symonds who wants to cut and the ball rolls over to backward point
slightly short of length, Martyn, who initially looks to come forward, rocks back and cuts it past point
defended off the front foot
runs down the track and swats it but finds the mid-off
on the middle and leg, Symonds shuffles across and turns it to long-leg
fullish on the off stump, Martyn leans forward, opens the face of the blade and runs it to backward-point
length delivery on the middle, Symonds rolls his wrists and gets the ball between square-leg and midwicket
slightly slower delivery, outside the off, Martyn cuts but doesn't get much power behind that stroke and the ball rolls over to point
almost at the block-hole and Martyn drives it powerfully back down the track where Taylor puts his right hand out to make the stop
length delivery on the off, punched to cover
spears in full and on the legs, flicked away but straight to midwicket
short and outside off, cut hard but straight to the sweeper cover
slower ball but mis-directed. It sails down the leg side
another slower delivery and on the stumps this time, pushed down the ground
overpitched outside the off, driven to long-off
yet another slower one on the middle, turned to midwicket
short of a length and angling into middle and leg, flicked off the pads to midwicket
just short of a length on off stump, dabbed on the leg side for one
full toss on leg stump, Symonds backs away, makes room and hits down the ground
full length on off and middle, Martyn makes room and drives to cover
slower ball outside of stump, Martyn picked that and ran it down to third man
full and homing in on leg stump, Symonds flicks it to midwicket
on the stumps but Martyn backs away and cuts it past point.
comes down the track but Gayle holds back the length and Symond pushes it to the on side
wide down the leg side
on the legs, may be Gayle is worrying about Martyn backing away to cut, and worked around the corner
beaten outside the off as Martyn goes for his late-cut
driven down the ground to long-on
in the slot and Symonds scythes it through the line, swinging it over wide midwicket
on the legs, fullish, Symonds takes his left foot outside the line and heaves it over midwicket
slower ball ends up a low full-toss on the middle, Symonds paddle sweeps it behind square-leg
overpitched on the off, drilled to long-on
slower ball outside the off stump and Martyn waits for the ball to arrive and pushes it to long-on. Fifty up for Martyn.
on the middle, and Martyn backs away and taps it to backward point.
paddle sweep goes awry. He is through his shot before the ball arrives and it runs off the edge to right of short third-man
swept to long-leg
take that! no cute paddle sweep attempted this time. Instead, he plonks his left foot out and swings it over long-on. Symonds has made the West Indians bleed 20 runs in last 6 balls.
pushed towards midwicket and they cross over for a single
appeal for lbw as Martyn attempts to sweep but going down leg
Bradshaw begins his new spell with a well-directed yorker. Symonds backs away but can only dig it out to the off side
Martyn gets under the ball but hits it straight into the waiting palms of Runako Morton at long-off. But he has done his job, 52 from 77 balls with seven fours.
Clarke is greeted to the crease with a delivery slanting across him and is beaten as he ends up pushing inside the line
tip and run. Clarke leans forward, drops the ball close on the off side and they hurry through for a single
half-edged, half-steered past the diving short third-man. outside the off stump and Symonds has a slash at it, gets an outside edge.
on the leg and middle, turned towards midwicket and will retain the strike
on the legs, turned past square-leg and Symonds turns back blind for the second run and , despite an direct-hit, he makes it in time.
from round the sticks, fullish on the middle, driven down the ground to long-on
tossed on the legs, turned past square-leg and this time they will have to make do with a single as Clarke slips while trying to turn back.
on the leg and middle, turning in, played back to the bowler
turns in from outside the leg, Symonds pushes at it, the inside-edge takes the ball past square-leg
runs down the track to the pitch of the ball and drives it to long-on
full and pushed across Clarke who keeps his left foot out and slices it, in the air, over cover and to the right of the sweeper cover
slanted across, run down to the third-man region
Symonds 19th ODI fifty is up. An length-delivery on the middle and off and Symonds taps it close on the off side and they cross over for a single
just outside the off stump, steered to short third-man region
right up in the blockhole, Symonds can only dig it out, back to the bowler
Fullish outside the off stump, Symonds carves it over cover point and Taylor runs across and uses his boots to kick the ball in. Bradshaw finishes his quota of 10 overs
beaten outside the off. Clarke backs away and tries to cut
makes contact this time, cut to backward point
Lara's gamble works. Symonds comes down the track and swings over deep backward square-leg but can't beat the man stationed at deep. Crucial breakthrough for West Indies.
full on the legs, turned to midwicket
driven down the ground
Hussey attempts to sweep, doesn't connect properly and the inside edge takes it  to the on side
fullish, just outside the off stump, driven to cover
beaten outside off as Hussey tries to dab it down to the third-man region
driven past cover
attempted yorker turns into low full-toss, flicked past square-leg
wide down the leg side and Baugh, who is standing up, makes an excellent gathering.
another low full-toss, driven to long-on

slower ball, rolled his wrists over and delivered like an off break, 
Hussey waits for it and runs it down to third-man
floated on the off stump, steered past point
on the stumps, Clarke presses back and pushes it past midwicket. Mix-up between Lara, inside the circle, and the man at the deep midwicket about who would make the stop results in an extra run
slightly short and pulled away to backward square-leg where Morton gets across to make a neat stop
comes down the track, the ball is held back a bit, Clarke adjusts to push it to Lara at midwicket
appeal for lbw but turned down. bit of turn from the middle, Clarke is hit on the knee roll as he attempts to work it to the on side
driven to widish long-on
turns in from outside off, pushed to the off side
comes down the track and turns it to the leg side
pushed across flat and outside the off stump, Clarke reaches for it to slice over cover
comes down the track, driven to widish long-off
fires in that one flat, pulled to deep midwicket
swept from outside the off stump, behind square-leg
full and on the leg and middle, driven to midwicket and they run with the stroke
on the middle and leg, driven down long-on
on the legs, worked behind square-leg
on the stumps but Clarke backs, leaving his stumps exposed, and cuts it to deep cover
fullish on the middle and off, driven to long-off
fired in quick on the legs, turned to long-leg. 200 is up.

Sarwan's ploy of bowling from round the sticks, and turning it from outside the leg stump works again. Clarke runs down the track, tries to get outside the line and attempts to heave it  but gets a top-edge that takes the ball to cover
turns in from outside off, pushed back to the bowler
comes down the track but only hits it back to Sarwan
swept from outside the off stump
low full-toss, Haddin turns it past square-leg to rotate the strike back to Hussey
six over cover! Hussey waltzed down the track and drove it inside-out. Lovely shot.
yes sir, he starts off with a slower one and Haddin almost hit it back straight to him. ends up driving it, in the air, through mid-off
on the legs, Hussey would be kicking himself for turning it straight to short fine-leg

another slower ball, ends up as a half-tracker and hammered past the bowler for a astounding six! He stands up tall, waits for the ball to arrive and nonchalantly hoicks it over Bravo' head and over the straight boundary
driven, in the air, past Bravo and to long-off and they scamper through for the second run
fullish on the stumps, driven down the ground
slower ball but ends up outside the leg stump. Baugh fumbles and the ball rolls past the helmet behind him - 5 penalty runs if it had hit that- and they cross over.
swung over midwicket but can't beat the man at deep
pushed to mid-off and they jog through for a single. Hussey will be on strike now.
low full-toss , swatted down the ground but will have to be contend with just a single.
another low full-toss, dipping in on the boots, driven to the on side
slower ball - a off break and Hussey adjusts to steer it past point
lovely yorker. tails in late and dips on the middle, Haddin brings his bat down in a hurry to keep it out.
Not quite there at the block-hole, driven to long-off and throw is fired in at the wicketkeeper's end to kill any thought about the second run
low full-toss on the middle and leg, turned to Lara, at midwicket, who has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses. If he had hit, Haddin would have been on his bike.
another low full-toss on the stumps, Hussey backs away to have slash at it, gets an inside-edge that takes the ball past the short fine-leg
full and on the leg and middle, worked past square-leg and they run hard to complete the second run. Hussey will retain the strike.
yorker and dug out to extra cover
fullish on the off stump line, driven to long-off

attempted yorker turns into a low full-toss on the middle, Hussey backs away and swings it past midwicket to finish the innings off in style.  Again Hussey displays a cool head to steer his side to a very healthy total.

inn2.comm: and he strikes first ball! A great delivery, full and fast right in the blockhole, some genuine late swing there and Gayle is rapped right in front middle stump, that was a toe-crusher, Lee and the rest let out a vociferous appeal and Asad Rauf has little hesitation in raising the finger, what a start for Australia as Gayle limps off
a no-ball, oversteps as he fires in full delivery outside off stump which Morton plays back to him
a good delivery outside off stump, Morton hustles to defend off the back foot
quicker on a short length on middle and off, nips back to strike Morton high on the thigh but the ball would have carried on over the stumps
similar delivery and again Morton is caught hopping and is rapped on the thigh
lands on middle and leg, turned straight to square leg
outside off stump, driven at and edged to thirdman for a single
left alone outside the off stump
gets behind it and defends to the off side
opens the face off the bat runs it down to thirdman
overpitched delivery outside the off stump, driven well to long off fence
defends compactly to the off side
short lifting delivery outside the off stump, goes for the drive and inside edges on the track
on the leg and middle angled to point
oversteps, on the leg and middle, beats the batsman, goes across him.
worked to square leg
short lifting delivery outside the off stump, looking for the cut, mistimes it
left alone outside the off stump
hurries of the wicket, Morton pushes gently to the off side
driven to Symonds at cover
comes into Morton, defends well to the off side
comes in again, defends with an open face to point
fuller on the pads, looks to flick but gets clipped on the pads
driven wonderfully well to the extra-cover fence
overpitched on the legs, Chanderapaul mistimes the flick in the air towards midwicket, Katich takes the catch
driven to Martyn at mid on
driven once again straight to Martyn
on the off and middle, driven off the back foot to backward-point
short in length, driven off the back foot to Symonds, who is very quick at this position
wide outside the off stump, Sarwan watches and lets it go through to Haddin
on the middle and leg, turned behind square leg to Katich in the deep, comes back for the second run
left alone outside the off stump
outside the off stump, Sarwan watches it go by through to Haddin
drives handsomely to mid off but for no runs
plays forward, raps him on the pad

and he's gone! A good quick delivery on the stumps, plays down the wrong line and is rapped in front of middle and leg, a good shout and the verdict is upheld, Morton's painstaking innings of 31 deliveries with opening his account comes to an end
good ball on the stumps, Sarwan hops and defends
width offered, cut to point, Lara wanted the single and had to hurry to beat Clarke's throw
a good length on off stump, quick to get into his defense
similar ball outside off stump, Sarwan defends towards point, a tidy over from McGrath
fullish outside off and Lara shoulders arms
fuller outside off and he drives that into the covers
glorious! Overpitched outside off again and he leans into that and drives between point and cover for four, classic Lara stroke
full outside off and dying and Lara leaves it alone, low bounce for Haddin behind the stumps
again outside off and Lara looks at it and leaves it alone
this one lands outside off again and comes in, Lara quickly defends towards point
good length on middle and off, he stands tall and turns that to the onside, square leg moves in and denies them a run
a no-ball as McGrath oversteps, lands outside off and Sarwan defends to the offside
good ball lands outside off and moves away, Sarwan thinks about the shot but just manages to withdraw the bat at the last minute
short outside off, room is not really there to cut, Sarwan does anyways and is cramped, ball shoots to Clarke at point on the bounce
fullish outside off stump, some late movement which Sarwan picks and shoulders arms
fullish outside off and moves the other way, Sarwan gets nowhere and flashes at it, beaten comprehensively
good length outside off, Sarwan hops in the crease and chops that into the off side, Clarke swoops in and fires in a throw at Lara's end just to make sure he was awake
lands outside off stump, steered to point
good ball swinging into off stump, Lara gets forward and defends to point
fuller this time on off, Lara gets across and drives to mid-on who fires in a throw, they resist the single
drifts down leg and its helped to wide of square leg for a single
quick and full on middle and off, Sarwan defends back to the bowler
drifts to middle and leg, Sarwan jumps and just drops that it his feet, Lara calls for a quick run and they hustle through
full on middle and off, driven to Lee at mid-on who doesnt field cleanly and gives up a single that was never on
good ball on off, Lara gets forward and pushes that to cover
lands on middle and leg and its worked to midwicket
good length on off stump, Lara gets back in the crease and turns that to midwicket again
a no-ball, lands on a good length outside off, Lara goes for an ambitious swipe across the line and fails to make contact
better ball on off stump and its defended to point
lands on a good length on leg, Lara moves and tries to work that to square leg, ball clips the bat then pad and Watson appeals rather mutedly but Rauf hands him back his hat
a good length outside off, steered past gully for a single
good delivery on the stumps, uses the soft hands to push that in front over cover for a sharp single
gets his man! A great delivery that lands outside off and moves in a shade, Lara defends and gets a tickle off the outside edge through to Haddin, West Indies in deep trouble
a good ball on off, lands and seams over the top of off stump as Bravo shoulders arms
middle and off line, Bravo looks to tuck it to the on side but makes poor contact
middle and off and moving away over the stumps, again Bravo shoulders arms and gets struck high on the thigh
short and wide and its cut into covers for one
drifts to leg and its turned around the corner towards square leg
good ball on off stump, Sarwan stands and defends back to Lee
fullish outside off, Sarwan flashes hard at it, ball flies in the gap at gully and down to third man
full on off stump, close to a yorker length, well flicked into the midwicket region
good full delivery on off, dug out into the covers
angling across him from off stump and he shoulders arms watchfully, Haddin collects
similar delivery, closer to the stumps this time, and again Bravo watches it through as he covers his stumps
slighly shorter and he tries to turn that from outside off to square lega and gets rapped on the pad, but that was well outside the stumps
drifts to middle and off and he quickly gets into position and turns it in front of square leg
good length on off stump, gets onto the front foot and drives that to mid-off
shorter this time outside off and he cuts that to Clarke at point
short outside off, Bravo jumps and manages to keep that down and glides it past slip and gully for one
fuller outside off and its driven loosely to Martyn at mid-off
good, slow delivery outside off, almost a legcutter and it dies on Sarwan as he leaves it alone
shorter and quicker outside off and Sarwan defends into the covers
more runs, this one pitches on leg and is just helped around the corner past a diving Haddin for four, two boundaries to Sarwan to round off the over
good length ball outside off, Bravo is taken by the bounce but manages to defend it towards point
another good rising delivery on middle and off, Bravo drops the hands and the ball trickles to the onside, Sarwan calls for the run and they scamper through
slower outside off stump, Sarwan pushes that to the left of Clarke at point and Bravo calls for the run
fuller delivery outside off and he lets it through
another good delivery moving away from outside off, Bravo gets a foot forward and shoulders arms
drifts to middle and off, Bravo walks across and tucks that to midwicket and calls for the run
short and wide and he goes back and cuts that down to third man for a single, the 50 comes up for West Indies
a slow halfvolley outside off stump, Sarwan gets to the pitch of it and drives that to cover
dropped in short, Sarwan quickly onto that and pulls that in the air tantalisingly close to Ponting at midwicket who dives to his right but cant get a hand to it, the ball goes to the ropes
good lifting ball outside off stump, Sarwan chases it but makes no contact
a good length ball on the stumps, Sarwan goes back instead of forward and just manages to keep that out
a driveable length outside off, all he can do is push that to Martyn at mid-off
off spin it is, flighted outside off stump, Bravo looks to flick and gets rapped, Symonds appeals but Benson says nope
flighted on off, Bravo forward and gets hit on the pad again, another loud appeal but Benson thinks that would have carried over the stumps
middle and off and its defended back to Symonds
middle and leg, he tucks that around the corner

simple dismissal! Dropped in short outside off, Bravo doesnt get on top of it, takes the eyes off it going for some sort of hook but all he does is pull that tamely to Ponting at short midwicket who takes one step to his right and pouches the simplest of chances, Watson strikes and Australia well on top
good ball on the stumps, Hinds goes back and defends to Clarke at point
a no-ball, and would have been wide too as it swings down leg stump, Haddin dives to his right and pulls off a fine take
good length ball outside off, Hinds looks to run that down but misses and gets rapped behind the pad
another beauty that lands outside off and beats the outer edge of Hinds' forward prod

bowled! A good, swinging delivery on off stump, Hinds' feet go nowhere as he goes for an expansive drive and he ends up playing all over that, the ball goes on to hit off stump, his poor run of form continues, Watson whoops it up with his team-mates
almost a third! A good ball lands outside off and rises, Smith pokes at it and gets the edge but it lands just in front of second slip, what a good over for Australia
flighted on off, Sarwan forward and defends
slower through the air, good flight, Sarwan forward and tries to tickle it around the corner, ball just misses the leg stump, that was close
looped over on middle and off, he goes to defend and gets clipped on the pad
ohh! Tossed up outside off, Smith goes for a wild swipe across the line and misses, the bat swings out of his hands and just misses Haddin's head, what reflexes from the 'keeper
middle and off, turned to the on side
middle and leg, worked fine for a single
full outside off and its left alone
slower, yorker-length delivery on off stump and its pushed back to Watson
quicker and moving down leg, clips Sarwan's pad and rolls back to Watson
shot! Gives him the charge, makes room and picks that from off stump and smashes it over covers for four
he strays to middle and leg and its flicked to midwicket for a single
good length delivery outside off, he stands and defends to cover
flighted outside off stump, well picked up and swiped through midwicket
tossed up outside off again, Smith gets a foot forward and lofts that over mid-on for four
even better! Tossed up again outside off, he gets down and slams it across the line for a huge six over deep midwicket, top shot from Smith!
tossed up again on off, gets forward and flicks it to mid-on for one
shot! Picked from outside off stump for a glorious pull over midwicket for six
short outside off, cut straight to point
short again, cut past point this time for one down to the sweeper in the deep
overpitched and its driven beatifully in the gap on the off side for four
banged in over his head and its called wide
quick on the stumps and its defended into the covers
banged in over his head and its called wide
full outside off stump and he shoulders arms
he oversteps this time, a full ball on the stumps is driven to mid-on
flighted outside off, he goes forward and drives to point
quicker on the stumps and he defends off the back foot
short and wide and he cracks that in the gap at gully and point for four
tossed up on off, defended back to Clarke
good ball lands outside off and moves in to nip him high on the knee roll, too high for an appeal though
shorter on middle and leg, he looks to pull but gets hit in the midriff, ball loops over Haddin for legbyes

run out! A good length delivery on middle and off, Smith goes back and works it to the on side, he starts to run, so does Sarwan, but they get all muddled up as Ponting dashes across from mid-on and in one smooth action collects the ball, turns, and fires in a super direct hit to get Sarwan out my miles, fine effort from the Australian captain, he doesnt miss many
good ball outside off, he stands tall and punches to cover
banged in short, Smith gets into position and pulls that in the air past square leg for one to the man on the ropes
short on middle and off, and Baugh just tucks that in front of square for a single to get off the mark and retain the strike
flighted on off stump, Baughs sweeps against the spin past square leg
tossed up outside off and its left alone
on the stumps and its driven back down the ground to where Katich does good work from long-on to save runs at the ropes
middle and leg and Baugh goes back and across to tickle it around the corner
well tossed up outside off and Baugh gets into stride and defends back to Clarke
simple dismissal! Overpitched outside off stump and Smith flicks that on the up and straight into the hands of Ponting at short midwicket, he goes for a quick 30 and Lee gets another to his name
moves to around the wicket, fires in a good length delivery on off, Bradshaw goes back and defends
similar delivery and Bradshaw gets right behind it and defends back to Lee in his follow-through

gone! Fractionally wider of off stump and inviting the drive, Bradshaw obliges but doesnt get to the pitch of it, flashes the drive and gets an edge through to Braddin for a simple take, Lee bursts into his smile as he looks back at the umpire, but everyone knows the result on that one, and Bradshaw hasnt troubled the scorers any, one wicket left to take for Australia
good length delivery on the stumps, Taylor gets behind it and defends back to Lee
very good delivery outside off, forces Taylor to hop and defend it, ball drops off the bat very close to the off stump
flatter on off, Baugh back and defends back to Clarke
spins past him from outside off as he leaves it alone
good flight on that one as it spins past Baugh's bat
middle and leg, Baugh looks to lap it around the corner and the ball smacks into the side of Haddin's head, ouch
quicker outside off and it beats Baugh's attempted cut
tossed up outside off stump, Baugh gets to the pitch of it and drives in the gap on the offside to retain strike
a nice lifter outside off cramps him for room, Baugh does well to sway out of harm's way

all over! Lee bangs this one in short on middle and leg, Baugh takes his eyes off it as it hurries onto him, his attempted hook goes nowhere but up in the air for Haddin to take a few steps to his left and take a simple catch, Lee gets four to his name and Australia have lifted the DLF Cup by 127 runs
